<h1>Simulation Triggers</h1>
<p>Triggers provide a way for simulation variables to affect each other. For example, 
  when spending on sanitation increases above a certain level this may trigger 
  the number of rats in the city to decrease.</p>
<p>[More continuous influences, such as embedded formulas, will be added soon.]</p>
